channel.title: What is your favorite Classic Auxy song?
channel.description:
(This Post is most likely for old Auxy users.)
This post is remembering the many years Auxy has gone through. It is almost 2018, and I want to know what your favorite nostalgic Auxy song was!
This could be to old featured songs (For example, DeCruz - Far Out) or old demo songs, (For example, Marmalade)
My personal favorite is the Marmalade demo, and not the new one. What’s yours?

item.title: What is your favorite Classic Auxy song?
item.dc:creator: MrSerpent
item.description:
I’ve been listening to auxy songs for fun for a long time, here is a (partial) list of some keepers I’ve found over the years:

Rrammah - Oblivion
https://soundcloud.com/rrammah/oblivion

Produk - Nova
https://soundcloud.com/produkk/nova

Austin Haga - Opposites
https://soundcloud.com/austin_haga/opposites

Krute & Bradley Saint James - Sunshine
https://soundcloud.com/kruuute/sunshine-krute-x-bsj

notmiles - Riptide
https://soundcloud.com/not_miles/riptide

DHO - Yeah!
https://soundcloud.com/dhomusic/yeah

stereofield - Nocturne
https://soundcloud.com/ridgelinesound/rl002

crystldawn - absence
https://soundcloud.com/freeformrecs/crystldawn-absence

Southborne - Chasm
https://soundcloud.com/southborne/chasm

eohr - Flex
https://soundcloud.com/eohr/flex

these are all I can remember for now but there are a lot of good auxy tracks out there from all time periods and I recommend anyone who’s interested to hop across these accounts and other auxy accounts and you’ll find some great tunes.
